trend_summary: Across the series, scattered forest and farmland give way to new housing tracts, apartment blocks and wider roads. Built-up footprint grows mainly by infill and edge expansion, yet sizeable green corridors and the river valley persist, keeping overall suburban character despite rising density.
notable_changes: Clearing of central woodland for a large residential/commercial enclave.
Northern farmland converted to housing estates and service roads.
Expansion and reconfiguration of highway interchanges on the western edge.
Insertion of new apartment clusters along the river corridor.
Gradual reduction, but preservation, of interior green belts and parks.
